      "content": "Modern civilizations are typically characterized by complex social stratification, advanced technological capabilities, and highly specialized labor. They usually feature centralized political authority and a reliance on abstract institutions like formal education or legal systems. In contrast, \"primitive\" societies are often characterized by smaller, kinship-based groups with less complex social organization and subsistence lifestyles. These distinctions reflect a shift from localized, tradition-bound living to large-scale, industrialized societal structures.",
