      "content": "Yes, scholars often use concepts of \"stages of development\" to map these transitions, though this framework is heavily critiqued. Historically, the narrative suggests that groups moved from simpler, agrarian or tribal structures toward more complex, industrialized societies. However, many contemporary anthropologists are wary of this linear model, arguing that different cultures develop complexity in unique, non-comparable ways. They focus more on internal dynamics rather than a single, universal path to \"modernity.\"",
